    "&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The proposed front extension, by reason of its siting and\r\nexcessive depth would result in loss of light, overshadowing and outlook for\r\nthe occupiers of No. 37 Bancroft Gardens, to the detriment of their visual and\r\nresidential amenities, contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework\r\n(2023), Policy D3 D(7) of The&amp;nbsp; London Plan (2021), Core Policy CS1.B of\r\nthe Harrow Core Strategy (2012), Policy DM1 of the Harrow Development\r\nManagement Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary Planning\r\nDocument: Residential Design Guide (2010).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;The proposed front extension, by reason of its excessive\r\ndepth, width,&amp;nbsp;bulk and prominent siting, would give rise to an incongruous,\r\nbulky and unduly obtrusive form of development in the street scene and would\r\nfail to respect the pattern of development in the area, to the detriment of the\r\ncharacter and appearance of the host dwellinghouse, street scene and locality,\r\ncontrary to the high quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy\r\nFramework (2023), Policy D3 D(1) and D(11) of The&amp;nbsp; London Plan (2021),\r\nCore Policy CS1.B of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012), Policy DM1 of the Harrow\r\nDevelopment Management Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary\r\nPlanning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
